#: ../../R/room-temperature-IQ.rst:5
msgid "room-temperature IQ"
msgstr "room-temperature IQ"

#: ../../R/room-temperature-IQ.rst:7
msgid "quant\\."
msgstr "quant."

#: ../../R/room-temperature-IQ.rst:9
msgid ""
"[IBM] 80 or below (nominal room temperature is 72 degrees Fahrenheit, 22 "
"degrees Celsius). Used in describing the expected intelligence range of the "
":ref:`luser`\\. \"Well, but how's this interface going to play with the "
"room-temperature IQ crowd?\" See :ref:`drool-proof-paper`\\. This is a much "
"more insulting phrase in countries that use Celsius thermometers."
msgstr ""
"[IBM] 80以下(公称の室温は華氏72度、摂氏22度)。\\ :ref:`luser`\\ "
"に期待される知能の範囲を表すのに使われる。「ふむ、だがこのインターフェースは室温IQの連中相手にどう振る舞うんだろう?」\\ :ref:`drool-"
"proof-paper`\\ を参照。これは摂氏温度計を使う国々ではずっと侮辱的な表現である。"
